25/01/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- One policeman and four suspected terrorists were killed in a large-scale police operation Thursday (January 24th) against al-Qaeda followers in the southeastern Turkish province of Gaziantep.
Governor Suleyman Kamcı said police staged simultaneous raids on 18 purported hideouts.
Armed clashes erupted as terrorists opened fire on security forces.
The operation continued for 12 hours.
Four other police officers were injured, two of them seriously.
In all, 19 al-Qaeda suspects were arrested.
Kamcı added that an enormous amount of guns, ammunition and explosives were found, indicating that al-Qaeda was planning "sensational attacks in Turkey".
(Zaman, Sabah - 25/01/08;
NTV, Reuters, AFP, DW - 24/01/08)
